As of the [[2020 United States census]], there were 419 people, 162 households, and 105 families residing in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Manalapan+town;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2020.S1101|access-date=July 2, 2023|website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

As of the [[2010 United States census]], there were 406 people, 152 households, and 104 families residing in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=HOUSEHOLDS AND FAMILIES|url=https://data.census.gov/table?q=Manalapan+town;+Florida+&tid=ACSST5Y2010.S1101|access-date=September 26, 2023|website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

===2000 census===
As of the census<ref name="GR2" /> of 2000, there were 321 people, 167 households, and 107 families residing in the town. The population density was {{convert|712.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 271 housing units at an average density of {{convert|601.7|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the town was 98.13% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]] (95% were [[Non-Hispanic White]]),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.muninetguide.com/states/florida/municipality/Manalapan.php |title=Demographics of Manalapan, FL |publisher=MuniNetGuide.com |access-date=November 23, 2007}}</ref> 1.56% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 0.31% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]]. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] residents of any race were 3.12% of the population.

As of 2000, there were 167 households, out of which 9.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 59.9% were married couples living together, 2.4% had a female householder with no husband present, and 35.9% were non-families. 30.5% of all households were made up of individuals, and 21.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 1.92 and the average family size was 2.33.

In 2000, 7.8% of the population was under the age of 18, 2.2% was from 18 to 24, 13.4% from 25 to 44, 35.8% from 45 to 64, and 40.8% was 65 years of age or older. The median age was 61 years. For every 100 females, there were 94.5 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 91.0 males.

In 2000, the median income for a household in the town was $127,819, and the median income for a family was $117,051. Males had a median income of over $100,000 versus $36,250 for females. The per capita income for the town was $143,729. About 3.7% of families and 5.9% of the population were below the [[poverty threshold|poverty line]], including none of those under age 18 and 4.3% of those age 65 or over.

Those who spoke only [[English language|English]] at home accounted for 98.54% of the population, while [[French language|French]] was a [[home language]] of 1.45%.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mla.org/map_data_results&state_id=12&county_id=&mode=place&zip=&place_id=42700&cty_id=&ll=&a=&ea=&order=r |title=MLA Data Center Results for Manalapan, Florida |publisher=[[Modern Language Association]] |access-date=November 23, 2007}}</ref>

